-- SAP, Volkswagen Shares May Move in Frankfurt: German Equity Market Preview
-- Julie Cruz
-- 2010-07-21T06:34:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/sap-volkswagen-shares-may-be-active-equity-market-preview-for-germany.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Germany. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the last close.  
 The benchmark DAX Index lost 0.7 percent to 5,967.49
yesterday. DAX Index futures expiring in September rose 0.9
percent as of 8:33 a.m. in Frankfurt.  
 SAP AG  (SAP GY): The world’s biggest maker of business-
management software won European Union approval to acquire
Sybase Inc. in a transaction valued at $5.8 billion to help SAP
fend off competition from Oracle Corp. The shares fell 1.1
percent to 36.78 euros.  
 Volkswagen AG  (VOW3 GY): Europe’s largest carmaker will
probably begin building an engine plant in Mexico in September,
to supply its North American assembly lines starting in 2013,
Handelsblatt reported, citing  Wolfgang Hatz , VW’s head of engine
development. The shares dropped 0.6 percent to 74.19 euros.  
